The paper deals with the problem of testing whether a given collection of vectors can be transformed into sparse vectors, which is a fundamental problem in signal processing, statistics, and machine learning. This problem is closely related to dictionary learning, which is a well-studied topic in the information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and data structures (cs.DS) communities. The paper also involves the use of linear queries and the analysis of gaussian width, which are topics in signal processing (cs.SP) and mathematical modeling (cs.MM). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
